Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.98,0:00:14.16,English,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,975)}I guess it is pretty simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.98,0:00:14.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,930)} 也许这个视频真的很简单
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.74,0:00:15.87,English,,0,0,0,,Yep, told ya so!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.74,0:00:15.87,Chinese,,0,0,0,,是啊，早就跟你说了
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.88,0:00:18.54,English,,0,0,0,,I am in fact capable of making shorter videos.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.88,0:00:18.54,Chinese,,0,0,0,,实际上我能做短视频
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.54,0:00:21.14,English,,0,0,0,,Well, this gag sure isn’t helping with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.54,0:00:21.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,行了吧，你说了也没用
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.14,0:00:26.78,English,,0,0,0,,Indeed. so let’s introduce the topic and talk about these little cassette adapter thingies.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.14,0:00:26.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,,好吧，那我们少说废话，来谈下磁带转换器吧
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.78,0:00:35.54,English,,0,0,0,,{\fs50\fn文泉驿等宽微米黑\pos(990,80)}注：淘宝售价9元左右
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.78,0:00:33.24,English,,0,0,0,,If you have an older car which only has a cassette deck but you need your sweet AUX JACK,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.78,0:00:33.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果你有一辆只有磁带卡座的老爷车，而你需要用亲切的音频插座的话
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.24,0:00:35.54,English,,0,0,0,,well, you’ll probably have used one of these before.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.24,0:00:35.54,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那么你一定会用过这个
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.54,0:00:37.62,English,,0,0,0,,And they’ve been around for quite a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.54,0:00:37.62,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而且这玩意已经在世很多年了
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.62,0:00:40.54,English,,0,0,0,,Back when a CD Walkman was the height of sophistication,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.62,0:00:40.54,Chinese,,0,0,0,,早在CD Walkman十分成熟的时候
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.54,0:00:42.46,English,,0,0,0,,you could modernize your car with one of these
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.54,0:00:42.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你会在你的车上装上这个"现代化"的玩意
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.46,0:00:46.50,English,,0,0,0,,and be enjoying the best the world of Compact Disc has to offer.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.46,0:00:46.50,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然后享受CD带来的美妙音质
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.50,0:00:47.68,English,,0,0,0,,Ever wonder how they work?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.50,0:00:47.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你们有想过它们是怎么工作的吗
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.88,0:00:49.42,English,,0,0,0,,Only all the time!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.88,0:00:49.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,,是啊，你可倒是说啊
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.76,0:00:54.10,English,,0,0,0,,No! Stop. That gag is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.76,0:00:54.10,Chinese,,0,0,0,,嘿，说你呢！再说的话，出去！
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.48,0:00:59.92,English,,0,0,0,,To understand how this works, we first need to understand a bit about the technology behind audio tape.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.48,0:00:59.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,为了了解它的原理，我们需要些磁带背后的原理
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.92,0:01:02.52,English,,0,0,0,,Fricken’ tapes. How do they work?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.92,0:01:02.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这没人要的外语磁带到底是怎么发出声音的？
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.52,0:01:03.54,English,,0,0,0,,Magnets!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.52,0:01:03.54,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那自然是————磁力！
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.54,0:01:07.98,English,,0,0,0,,Magnetic tape is some pretty neat stuff, though it’s not groovy I’ll tell you that.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.54,0:01:07.98,Chinese,,0,0,0,,磁带是个好玩意，当然现在说有点落款
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.98,0:01:10.00,English,,0,0,0,,Instead it’s particular.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.98,0:01:10.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,实际上这个还挺特别的
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.00,0:01:14.72,English,,0,0,0,,Conventional type I audio tape is simply a thin ribbon of plastic backing which has a
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.00,0:01:14.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一般的一类磁带基本上就是一层很薄的塑料
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.72,0:01:18.47,English,,0,0,0,,bunch of finely ground-up rust smeared all over it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.72,0:01:18.47,Chinese,,0,0,0,,上面铺满了一层铁锈（实际上是四氧化三铁）
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.47,0:01:23.08,English,,0,0,0,,The iron oxide particles can be magnetized with a little help from an electromagnet.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.47,0:01:23.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这些氧化铁粒子可以通过电磁铁给磁化
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.08,0:01:27.66,English,,0,0,0,,Inside a cassette deck (or really any tape deck at all), a special electromagnet called
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.08,0:01:27.66,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在卡座里（不管是什么磁带的），一块称作
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.66,0:01:31.22,English,,0,0,0,,the head makes contact with the tape as it travels past it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.66,0:01:31.22,Chinese,,0,0,0,,磁头的特制电磁铁会与通过的磁带接触
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.22,0:01:31.86,English,,0,0,0,,Fun fact!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.22,0:01:31.86,Chinese,,0,0,0,,还挺好玩的哈！
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.22,0:01:31.86,English,,0,0,0,,{\fn文泉驿等宽微米黑\pos(960,80)}注：不知道现在初中物理课本STS环节还有这个吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.86,0:01:34.58,English,,0,0,0,,In video tape, the heads do the traveling!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.86,0:01:34.58,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在视频磁带中，磁头是会动的！
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.58,0:01:38.14,English,,0,0,0,,I made a video waaaaay long ago about that if you’re interested.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.58,0:01:38.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你感兴趣的话，我老久之前做了一个视频
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.14,0:01:43.72,English,,0,0,0,,Now, because the tape is made of fine particles, different spots along its length can be magnetized
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.14,0:01:43.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那么，鉴于磁带上面铺满了细小的铁颗粒，这条磁带的各个部分都可以
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.72,0:01:45.22,English,,0,0,0,,to different extents.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.72,0:01:45.22,Chinese,,0,0,0,,被磁化为不同磁性
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.22,0:01:50.98,English,,0,0,0,,Think of it like a bunch of teeny tiny bits of metal that can more or less be individually magnetized.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.22,0:01:50.98,Chinese,,0,0,0,,想象一下，一堆十分细小的铁颗粒可以分别给磁化
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.98,0:01:55.72,English,,0,0,0,,If you move this granular tape across the head as it gets all electromagnety,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.98,0:01:55.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果你将这些有磁性颗粒的带子与电磁铁摩擦的话
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.72,0:02:00.82,English,,0,0,0,,you will end up with a linear representation of how intense the magnetic field the head created
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.72,0:02:00.82,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你最终将会得到一个线状的、清晰分明的、
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.82,0:02:02.20,English,,0,0,0,,was over time.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.82,0:02:02.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,由磁头一直画出来的磁场分布图
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.20,0:02:06.46,English,,0,0,0,,Spots that were exposed to a strong field will be strongly magnetized, and spots that
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.20,0:02:06.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,,暴露在超强磁场的部分会被磁化
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.46,0:02:09.48,English,,0,0,0,,weren’t exposed will be hardly magnetized at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.46,0:02:09.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,未被暴露在磁场的部分就基本没被磁化
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.48,0:02:14.76,English,,0,0,0,,Tie that magnetization level to some sort of signal, like perhaps audio,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.48,0:02:14.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而这种磁性变化就可以承载信息了，比如声音
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.76,0:02:18.07,English,,0,0,0,,and you will end up with that signal represented on the tape.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.76,0:02:18.07,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然后你就可以在磁带上录音了
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.08,0:02:22.94,English,,0,0,0,,Check out this neat video from Techmoan if you want to see what that signal actually looks like.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.08,0:02:22.94,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果你对信号的模样感兴趣的话，你可以看看Techmoan的这个视频
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.08,0:02:22.94,English,,0,0,0,,{\fn文泉驿等宽微米黑\pos(960,80)}注：3M制造的磁带磁性查看器：av99685974
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.94,0:02:26.72,English,,0,0,0,,The thing about electromagnets though is that they work backwards, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.94,0:02:26.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这个电磁铁不仅可以磁化磁带，还可以读取磁带
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.73,0:02:31.73,English,,0,0,0,,When a pre-recorded tape, complete with signals already on it, is run past the same head,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.73,0:02:31.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当提前录制好的磁带经过电磁铁的话的话，
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.73,0:02:33.90,English,,0,0,0,,the head can detect the signal!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.73,0:02:33.90,Chinese,,0,0,0,,磁头便可以侦测到信号啦
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.90,0:02:37.81,English,,0,0,0,,The changes in the magnetic field the head encounters as the magnetized tape travels
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.90,0:02:37.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,,磁头侦测到磁带的磁性变化会
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.81,0:02:41.50,English,,0,0,0,,past it induces a small current in its tiny little coils.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.81,0:02:41.50,Chinese,,0,0,0,,变成磁头线圈的微小电流
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.90,0:02:41.50,English,,0,0,0,,{\fn文泉驿等宽微米黑\pos(960,85)}注：请各位打开物理选修3-2，复习楞次定律，练习右手螺旋定则
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.50,0:02:46.04,English,,0,0,0,,Even though it’s just a bunch of tiny magnetized particles, it has the same effect as moving
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.50,0:02:46.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,尽管各个小磁铁很微小，当它们
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.04,0:02:50.84,English,,0,0,0,,a magnet past a coil of wire and will thus induce a current in that coil.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.04,0:02:50.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一起经过磁头时，它们形成的磁场会加强线圈的电流
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.84,0:02:55.00,English,,0,0,0,,This can be amplified to recreate the original signal, and thus sound,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.84,0:02:55.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这个电流可以放大，以产生原始信号
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.00,0:02:57.68,English,,0,0,0,,that was imparted on the tape when it was recorded.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.00,0:02:57.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那么声音也就是这么从磁带忠实地还原了
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.68,0:03:00.52,English,,0,0,0,,But of course, these adapters don’t have any tape in them.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.68,0:03:00.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但连派大星都知道，这些转接器里面都没有磁带呀
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.52,0:03:03.86,English,,0,0,0,,Wait, do they? No. No they don’t.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.52,0:03:03.86,Chinese,,0,0,0,,等会，真没有吗？嗯，是没有:-|
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.28,0:03:05.56,English,,0,0,0,,So what do they have?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.28,0:03:05.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那么这里面有什么名堂呢？
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.56,0:03:10.98,English,,0,0,0,,Well, for a start, an absurd number of incongruous logos that don’t belong anywhere near this thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.56,0:03:10.98,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你来看看这上面这堆和磁带八杆子打不着的玩意
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.98,0:03:13.04,English,,0,0,0,,Like, these are hilarious.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.98,0:03:13.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,看看这堆搞笑的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.04,0:03:15.54,English,,0,0,0,,Compact Disc? MiniDisc?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.04,0:03:15.54,Chinese,,0,0,0,,光盘？MiniDisc？
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.54,0:03:16.54,English,,0,0,0,,Pfft.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.54,0:03:16.54,Chinese,,0,0,0,,:-P
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.54,0:03:21.18,English,,0,0,0,,I like that the DCC logo is on here because you could kind of argue that it is a digital
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.54,0:03:21.18,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我喜欢这上面的DCC（数码磁带）标志，因为这好歹能让你想到
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.18,0:03:25.30,English,,0,0,0,,compact cassette so long as it’s plugged into like a CD player or whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.18,0:03:25.30,Chinese,,0,0,0,,磁带之类的东西，只要将其与CD播放器之类的东西相连接
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.30,0:03:28.26,English,,0,0,0,,Anyway, first consider what this does.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.30,0:03:28.26,Chinese,,0,0,0,,无论如何，咱先看看这个要干什么
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.26,0:03:32.76,English,,0,0,0,,It needs to produce the same effect as a real tape - so it needs to induce a current based
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.26,0:03:32.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这个要模拟磁带的作用的话，就要由卡座的磁头侦测到
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.76,0:03:39.48,English,,0,0,0,,on an audio signal in the playback head of whatever cassette player you’re using it in, but without actual tape.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.76,0:03:39.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,音频磁信号并转换为电流，但这回不是磁带产生音频磁信号
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.48,0:03:41.28,English,,0,0,0,,How could you go about doing that?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.48,0:03:41.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那这个是怎么做到的？
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.28,0:03:47.54,English,,0,0,0,,Well, remember that it’s the same head in most cassette decks that does the recording as the playing back.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.28,0:03:47.54,Chinese,,0,0,0,,请大家注意，大多数卡座都由一个磁头来录制和播放
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.54,0:03:52.78,English,,0,0,0,,The same head can be used as an electromagnet to record onto a tape or as a pickup coil
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.54,0:03:52.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,,同样的磁头可以当电磁铁，用来向磁带录音或
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.78,0:03:55.96,English,,0,0,0,,(or magnetic microphone if you will) to play a tape back.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.78,0:03:55.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,用作拾音线圈（或称电磁麦克风）用来播放磁带
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.96,0:04:01.02,English,,0,0,0,,And so, take a look at where the tape should be and you’ll find a tape head!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.96,0:04:01.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那么，咱来看看磁带本应在的位置呢，你会发现一个磁头！
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.03,0:04:05.68,English,,0,0,0,,A cassette adaptor like this uses a tape head just like the one in your cassette player,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.03,0:04:05.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,像这样的磁带转换器都会用和磁带播放器一样的磁头
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.68,0:04:09.76,English,,0,0,0,,and when it’s loaded in a cassette deck the two heads get real personal with one another.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.68,0:04:09.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在适配器装入卡座里后，这两个磁头会互相接触
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.76,0:04:14.56,English,,0,0,0,,The signal coming from the audio jack is pumped into that head, which is essentially coupled
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.76,0:04:14.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,从插口传过来的声音信号就会传入卡座磁头，这俩信号是
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.56,0:04:19.50,English,,0,0,0,,with the other, and the end result is that the audio signal from your phone, iPod, or whatever
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.56,0:04:19.50,Chinese,,0,0,0,,相吻合的，最终从你电话，随身听之类传入的信号
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.50,0:04:23.50,English,,0,0,0,,is injected right into the other head and thus into amplification circuitry
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.50,0:04:23.50,Chinese,,0,0,0,,会被传入另一个磁头，进而传入卡座的
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.50,0:04:27.84,English,,0,0,0,,of the cassette deck so it can play through your ‘96 Civic’s stereo or whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.50,0:04:27.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,放大电路，然后声音就可以从你的老爷车音箱中放出了
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.50,0:04:27.84,English,,0,0,0,,{\fn文泉驿等宽微米黑\pos(960,85)}注：原文Civic是1996年Honda生产的车
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.84,0:04:29.20,English,,0,0,0,,It’s that simple!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.84,0:04:29.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就是如此简单
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.20,0:04:31.46,English,,0,0,0,,Ah, but it’s not quite *so* simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.20,0:04:31.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,,额，但是这也没那么简单:-|
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.46,0:04:36.36,English,,0,0,0,,You see, many cassette decks have some sort of auto stop feature which works by detecting
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.46,0:04:36.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你瞧，很多磁带卡座都有通过侦测转轮是否旋转的
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.36,0:04:38.98,English,,0,0,0,,that the supply spool has stopped.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.36,0:04:38.98,Chinese,,0,0,0,,自动停止装置
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.98,0:04:43.70,English,,0,0,0,,Since there’s no actual tape in here at all, the supply spool wouldn’t turn on its own
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.98,0:04:43.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,,鉴于转换器内没有真正的磁带，转轮不会自己转起来
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.70,0:04:48.64,English,,0,0,0,,and the tape player would just… repeatedly stop, thinking it had reached the end of the tape.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.70,0:04:48.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,磁带播放机就会一直认为磁带已经放完
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.64,0:04:54.26,English,,0,0,0,,So, these usually contain a mechanism to cause the supply spool to turn with the take-up spool
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.64,0:04:54.26,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以，这些转换器自己还有一个机制来带动转轮
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.26,0:04:56.58,English,,0,0,0,,(the latter of which is turned by the cassette player itself)
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.26,0:04:56.58,Chinese,,0,0,0,,（转轮本身是由磁带转动的）
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.58,0:04:58.24,English,,0,0,0,,to prevent this from happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.58,0:04:58.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,以防止上述情况的发生
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.24,0:05:02.48,English,,0,0,0,,Some models will also prevent the reels from turning backwards, forcing an auto-reverse
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.24,0:05:02.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,有些型号还会阻止滚轮向反方向滚动，
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.49,0:05:07.02,English,,0,0,0,,deck into the forward position and ensuring the playback heads align with the little
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.49,0:05:07.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,让磁带走带装置一直向一个方向走，保证回放时拾音头与
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.02,0:05:10.20,English,,0,0,0,,broadcast heads, if you will, of the adapter.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.02,0:05:10.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,转换器的头相对齐
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.20,0:05:14.50,English,,0,0,0,,And is it really so simple as a playback head wired to an audio jack?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.20,0:05:14.50,Chinese,,0,0,0,,还有，难道这转换头和音频接口就接着一根线吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.50,0:05:20.38,English,,0,0,0,,Wouldn’t there need to be some sort of circuit in there to make the signal from the audio jack work?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.50,0:05:20.38,Chinese,,0,0,0,,难道不需要某种电路来让音频接口传来的信号工作？
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.38,0:05:23.17,English,,0,0,0,,Well, let’s find out by taking this apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.38,0:05:23.17,Chinese,,0,0,0,,来吧，一拆见真知:-)
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.17,0:05:24.71,English,,0,0,0,,It turns out that yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.17,0:05:24.71,Chinese,,0,0,0,,嗯，咱想的没错
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.71,0:05:26.94,English,,0,0,0,,It literally is that simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.71,0:05:26.94,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就是这么简单
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.94,0:05:30.24,English,,0,0,0,,Just the wires from the jack going right to the head.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.94,0:05:30.24,English,,0,0,0,,把插头传入的信号都给泵入转换头
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.25,0:05:34.97,English,,0,0,0,,Now, this head might be designed specifically for this purpose, though I kinda doubt it,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.25,0:05:34.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当然，这个头也许就是为了这个目的设计的，然而我很怀疑
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.97,0:05:37.06,English,,0,0,0,,but I suppose it is possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.97,0:05:37.06,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是这也许是真的呢
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.06,0:05:41.54,English,,0,0,0,,Since the same head can record and play on a typical cassette deck,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.06,0:05:41.54,Chinese,,0,0,0,,既然这个头既可以在卡座里用来录制和播放
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.54,0:05:43.62,English,,0,0,0,,could this be used in reverse?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.54,0:05:43.62,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那么这个可以将卡座信号传给转换器吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.62,0:05:50.24,English,,0,0,0,,What if I plugged this into an audio recorder, and hit record on this guy and fed a signal into it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.62,0:05:50.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,要是我把这个插进录音机，然后在卡座上向转换器输入信号的话
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.24,0:05:52.92,English,,0,0,0,,Would it be detectable by the audio recorder?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.24,0:05:52.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这信号会被录音机侦测到吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.92,0:05:54.72,English,,0,0,0,,Turns out, yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.92,0:05:54.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,实验结果是......可以！
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.72,0:05:57.98,English,,0,0,0,,Since the tape bias signal is well outside the audible range
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.72,0:05:57.98,Chinese,,0,0,0,,虽然磁带机的信号小到听不见
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.98,0:06:01.78,English,,0,0,0,,it doesn’t seem to affect things too much and you do in fact get a signal
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.98,0:06:01.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但这对实验结果没有影响，这确实能将
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.78,0:06:03.76,English,,0,0,0,,out of the cassette adapter. [tinny music is heard]
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.78,0:06:03.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,信号传入磁带转换器[尽管声音超小:-(]
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.76,0:06:09.18,English,,0,0,0,,While this is completely and totally useless, it is at least mildly interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.76,0:06:09.18,Chinese,,0,0,0,,尽管这个超级没用，但这个还是有点意思的
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.18,0:06:16.03,English,,0,0,0,,You might be surprised at the audio fidelity these things are capable of when used in the more normal fashion.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.18,0:06:16.03,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你会发现，就算按照现在的标准，这玩意的音质也是很不错的
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.04,0:06:20.22,English,,0,0,0,,For one thing, there is no tape noise at all when you use these.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.04,0:06:20.22,Chinese,,0,0,0,,比如说，这玩意没有磁带的谜之底噪
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.22,0:06:25.76,English,,0,0,0,,That hiss you hear from a tape is a result of the random structure of the magnetic particles themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.22,0:06:25.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而这堆噪音一般是由磁带上磁性粒子的不同造成的
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.76,0:06:29.88,English,,0,0,0,,You can’t get rid of it unless you use some clever tricks like Dolby Noise Reduction,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.76,0:06:29.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你不能去掉它，除非你用些特殊技巧，诸如杜比降噪
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.88,0:06:32.42,English,,0,0,0,,and even then it will still always be there a little bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.88,0:06:32.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而且就算开了，也是还有一点:-P
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.42,0:06:36.37,English,,0,0,0,,But if you don’t have any tape, well there’s no tape noise!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.42,0:06:36.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是你要是不用磁带的话，磁带底噪就没了
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.37,0:06:41.90,English,,0,0,0,,Seriously, to my ears using one of these, even a really terrible one like this, is basically
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.37,0:06:41.90,Chinese,,0,0,0,,说真的，对我而言，就算是用这个超级垃圾的转换器，
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.90,0:06:44.98,English,,0,0,0,,indistinguishable from a legitimate auxiliary input.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.90,0:06:44.98,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我也基本没法和有线输入的区分开
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.98,0:06:46.54,English,,0,0,0,,It’s pretty remarkable.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.98,0:06:46.54,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这个挺好
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.54,0:06:50.58,English,,0,0,0,,Oh and by the way, if you use these you want to make sure Dolby noise reduction is turned
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.54,0:06:50.58,Chinese,,0,0,0,,顺便说一句，你要用这个的话，你得关掉杜比降噪
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.59,0:06:54.96,English,,0,0,0,,off as otherwise you’re getting a needless reduction in fidelity in the form of a rather
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.59,0:06:54.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,要不然的话你就得到了一个有损音质
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.96,0:06:56.90,English,,0,0,0,,pronounced treble cut.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.96,0:06:56.90,Chinese,,0,0,0,,高频信号都给切了
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.90,0:07:01.46,English,,0,0,0,,And of course, for one last fun tidbit, since electronics keep getting smaller and cheaper
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.90,0:07:01.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,,最后来点好玩的花絮，因为目前电器部件越来越小
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.46,0:07:05.02,English,,0,0,0,,we now have Bluetooth versions of these!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.46,0:07:05.02,English,,0,0,0,,我们现在有适配蓝牙功能的了
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.02,0:07:11.00,English,,0,0,0,,These are actually really neat, they have a small battery with a micro USB port to recharge it,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.02,0:07:11.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这个东西很小，里面有块电池，通过微型USB接口充电
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.00,0:07:15.13,English,,0,0,0,,and a module inside allows you to pair your phone with it so you can play music through
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.00,0:07:15.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,里面还有蓝牙模块和手机适配，然后你就可以在这个适配器的帮助下
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.13,0:07:17.03,English,,0,0,0,,its little integrated head.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.13,0:07:17.03,Chinese,,0,0,0,,播放音乐了
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.03,0:07:21.08,English,,0,0,0,,They even give you a little microphone on a dongle for making hands-free calls.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.03,0:07:21.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这个里面甚至还有装着话筒，用来免提通话
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.08,0:07:26.48,English,,0,0,0,,I have no idea how well that part of it works but for $15 this thing is pretty neat.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.08,0:07:26.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我不知道这个的原理，但是这个玩意90块钱（15美元）也还行
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.48,0:07:30.54,English,,0,0,0,,I remember seeing in the past that someone had put out an MP3 player inside one of these
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.48,0:07:30.54,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我记得当年有人在这里面装个MP3
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.54,0:07:34.68,English,,0,0,0,,cassette shells complete with transport control buttons and its own headphone jack,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.54,0:07:34.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,还有控制按钮和音频接口
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.68,0:07:39.34,English,,0,0,0,,giving you hipster cred when you needed it and actually being useful in older cars.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.68,0:07:39.34,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当时用在老爷车上就显得潮:-|
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.34,0:07:46.40,English,,0,0,0,,I tried looking for it again but “cassette MP3 adapter” is a woefully unspecific term these days so…
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.34,0:07:46.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我在网上又找了一遍，但是“磁带MP3适配器”就是找不到......
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.40,0:07:51.14,English,,0,0,0,,well it’s probably still a thing but personally these Bluetooth ones which you can find in stores now
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.40,0:07:51.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,也许这个还会存在，但是现在咱们所找到的蓝牙适配器
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.14,0:07:56.92,English,,0,0,0,,would be my preference as they’re actually quite capable of modernizing an otherwise old car.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.14,0:07:56.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,真的在老爷车上面用十分合适
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.92,0:08:01.98,English,,0,0,0,,Well, that’s it! Can you believe it? A reasonably short video from Technology Connections!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.92,0:08:01.98,Chinese,,0,0,0,,好的，咱就这样？我真没想到咱频道也做了这个超级短的视频！
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.99,0:08:04.05,English,,0,0,0,,I feel like I must be dreaming.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.99,0:08:04.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我敢说我一定是在做梦
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.05,0:08:08.44,English,,0,0,0,,Anyway, time to leave you with everyone’s favorite smooth jazz hit.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.05,0:08:08.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,无论如何，我该用这个喜闻乐见的放松爵士乐来结束本期节目了
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.94,0:08:13.26,English,,0,0,0,,I… I can’t find the boombox I wanted for this shot so you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.94,0:08:13.26,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我找不到为这个节目准备的音响了
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.42,0:08:15.38,English,,0,0,0,,just pretend.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.42,0:08:15.38,Chinese,,0,0,0,,咱凑合一下
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.38,0:08:23.64,English,,0,0,0,,It’s kinda loud.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.38,0:08:23.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,还挺吵的呢
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.48,0:08:29.06,Chinese,,0,0,0,,以下是花絮部分
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.10,0:08:33.76,English,,0,0,0,,...but you need your sweet, sweet aux jack…
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.10,0:08:33.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是你得需要用你最喜欢的音频接口......
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.54,0:08:36.82,English,,0,0,0,,mm … that didn’t go well.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.54,0:08:36.82,Chinese,,0,0,0,,嗯，语气不对:-(
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.82,0:08:41.58,English,,0,0,0,,Conventional type I audio tape, which this is not, is simply a thin ribbon of plastic
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.82,0:08:41.58,Chinese,,0,0,0,,普通的一类磁带，当然这个不是，就是在一层薄塑料上......
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.58,0:08:43.30,English,,0,0,0,,… yeah I should get a type I tape.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.58,0:08:43.30,Chinese,,0,0,0,,不行，必须得拿一个一类带
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.76,0:08:44.78,English,,0,0,0,,Shouldn’t I?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.76,0:08:44.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我必须得拿吗?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.22,0:08:49.52,English,,0,0,0,,We can’t…. we can’t use this chrome tape because you pedants would be like
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.22,0:08:49.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我不能用这个二类带，要不总有人会钻牛角尖
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.52,0:08:52.12,English,,0,0,0,,“that’s a Maxell XLII! That’s not type I tape!”
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.52,0:08:52.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,“这个是Maxell XL 二类带！才不是啥一类带！”
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.12,0:08:53.62,English,,0,0,0,,so, gotta change it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.12,0:08:53.62,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以呢，咱必须得换!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.74,0:08:56.72,English,,0,0,0,,...and talk about these little cassette adapter thingies…
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.74,0:08:56.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,......然后咱谈一下这个磁带转换器......
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.72,0:08:58.70,English,,0,0,0,,hoo that was a bad…
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.72,0:08:58.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,,感觉不对
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.70,0:09:00.96,English,,0,0,0,,My nose itched. Probably a fine take.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.70,0:09:00.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,刚才鼻子难受，兴许一会就好了
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.98,0:09:05.58,English,,0,0,0,,...range it doesn't’ seem to affect things too much and you do in fact get a signal this is really rattly
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.98,0:09:05.58,Chinese,,0,0,0,,......听不见，但是这对实验结果没有影响，而且这确实能咯咯地......
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.58,0:09:08.00,English,,0,0,0,,That magnetization level to some so…
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.58,0:09:08.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那么磁性变化就可以......
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.00,0:09:09.06,English,,0,0,0,,Aagh!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.00,0:09:09.06,Chinese,,0,0,0,,啊！
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.06,0:09:09.72,English,,0,0,0,,Tie!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.06,0:09:09.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,Tie!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.72,0:09:10.72,English,,0,0,0,,That was the word, tie!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.72,0:09:10.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,怎么会是这个词？Tie!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.72,0:09:13.01,English,,0,0,0,,I was like “tie? That doesn't make any sense!”
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.72,0:09:13.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我当时想：“Tie? 放着根本不合适!”
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.01,0:09:14.54,English,,0,0,0,,No, you wrote that word.
